<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-10-17T20:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-10-17T20:36:00-05:00" n="1179" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1179">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/5258.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at Vera
                                    Cruz</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Vera Cruz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-10-17T19:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 17, 1912—7 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Felix Diaz, rebel general, with less than 1,000 men, expects hourly
                            attack by Federals. Consuls named committee who called upon Diaz,
                            requesting avoid righting within city. He promised or would advise, if
                            unavoidable, unless surprised. Gunboats against Diaz, under command
                            Azueta, threaten bombard barracks located center city. This evening
                            consuls requested me hold American steamer <hi rend="italic">Monterey</hi> await arrival next boat and <hi rend="italic">Des
                                Moines</hi> be sent back here at once. Telegraph communications
                            interrupted.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Canada.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>